Rachit Agrawal — Portfolio Design System
A standalone reference covering every design decision used across rachitagrawal146.github.io (the portfolio) and rachitagrawal146.github.io/game-algorithms-java (the games repo). Use this document alone to build any new page that stays consistent with the existing system.

1. Brand & Aesthetic
Mood: Dark editorial. Quiet, deliberate, confident. Think: a letterpress-era literary magazine translated into a terminal.

Principles:

Restraint over ornament — one accent colour (gold), two type families, lots of negative space.
Labels in mono, prose in serif or sans — the monospace labels act like small-caps in a print magazine.
Never square, never center-aligned by default — the page breathes from the left margin, like a book.
Every section is numbered (01 — About, 02 — The Journey …). Numbering is part of the identity.
Gold as light, not fill — the accent is used for glow, thin borders, sweep animations, and single characters in text. Never as a solid button background.
Slow motion — reveals are 0.7s, hero loads are 1s, halo breath is 6s. Nothing fast or bouncy.
