Typographic rules
Em dashes are &mdash; with spaces either side. Never hyphens for emphasis.
Quotes are curly: &ldquo;&rdquo; and &lsquo;&rsquo;.
Gold italic is the single most important device: use <em class="hero-headline-em"> or <span style="color: #c9a96e;"> to italicise a handful of words in gold inside a serif heading. This is the signature.
Labels use DM Mono at 9–10px, uppercase, with wide letter-spacing (0.2–0.3em). Never use mono for long prose.
Middle dots &middot; are the preferred separator in labels (16,000 ft &middot; May 2024).
Never underline links by default — use the animated underline on hover (see .link-anim).
4. Layout & Spacing
Containers
/* Tailwind config */
maxWidth: { content: "760px" }   /* The core column */

Main content column: max-w-content (760px) centered with mx-auto px-6.
Detail page column (projects.html): 780px.
Hero breakout: up to 1180px wide, using negative margins:
margin-left: calc((760px - min(1180px, 100vw - 3rem)) / 2);
margin-right: calc((760px - min(1180px, 100vw - 3rem)) / 2);

This lets the hero break out of the narrow column on desktop while collapsing cleanly at max-width: 880px.
Vertical rhythm
Major section: py-24 md:py-32 (6rem mobile, 8rem desktop).
Interstitial / aside (e.g. the Krishnamurti quote): py-16 md:py-20.
Card padding: p-8 md:p-10 (2rem → 2.5rem).
Section label bottom margin: margin-bottom: 3rem; (hard-coded in .section-label).
Gap between list items inside a section: space-y-10 for major, space-y-6 for dense lists.
Horizontal rules
.section-divider {
  border: none;
  border-top: 0.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
}

Used as <hr class="section-divider" /> between every major section. Never <hr> alone, never solid lines.

Breakpoints
max-width: 720px — stack photo grids to single column
max-width: 768px — mobile nav appears (bottom), desktop nav hides; hero stacks vertically
max-width: 880px — hero breakout ends, aligns to content column
5. Background Treatment
Noise overlay — the single most atmospheric detail. Apply to body::before:

body::before {
  content: '';
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 9999;
  pointer-events: none;
  opacity: 0.035;
  background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
  background-repeat: repeat;
  background-size: 256px 256px;
}

This is what makes the black feel like paper instead of OLED.

