8. Motion & Animations
Every animation respects prefers-reduced-motion: reduce. Every one.

8.1 Scroll reveal
.reveal {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(30px);
  transition: opacity 0.7s ease, transform 0.7s ease;
}
.reveal.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .reveal { opacity: 1; transform: none; transition: none; }
}

Activated by an IntersectionObserver that adds .visible when 15% of the element enters viewport. One-shot (observer disconnects per element).

8.2 Staggered children reveal
.reveal-stagger > * {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(16px);
  transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
}
.reveal-stagger.visible > * { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
.reveal-stagger.visible > *:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0s;    }
.reveal-stagger.visible > *:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 0.08s; }
.reveal-stagger.visible > *:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 0.16s; }
.reveal-stagger.visible > *:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 0.24s; }
.reveal-stagger.visible > *:nth-child(5) { transition-delay: 0.32s; }
.reveal-stagger.visible > *:nth-child(6) { transition-delay: 0.4s;  }

8.3 Hero load-in
.hero-load { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); animation: heroIn 1s ease 0.2s forwards; }
.hero-load-delay  { animation-delay: 0.5s; }
.hero-load-delay2 { animation-delay: 0.8s; }
.hero-load-delay3 { animation-delay: 1.1s; }
@keyframes heroIn { to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }

Sequential hero entry — tagline → headline → body → tags.

8.4 Shiny text sweep
See §6.2 above. Applied to every section label and hero tagline.

8.5 Portrait halo breath
Infinite breathing pulse on the hero portrait glow (see §6.9).

8.6 Gold blob cursor (desktop only)
A reactbits-style gooey cursor that follows the mouse with 3 trailing blobs. Merged via SVG feGaussianBlur + feColorMatrix goo filter.

Disabled on @media (hover: none) and @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce).

8.7 Scroll progress bar
.scroll-progress {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0; left: 0;
  height: 2px;
  width: 0%;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #c9a96e, #e8d5b0);
  z-index: 200;
}

Width set in JS from window.scrollY / (documentHeight - windowHeight).

8.8 Typing effect (hero)
The hero headline types out over an invisible placeholder that reserves layout space (prevents shift):

<h1 class="hero-headline font-display italic">
  <span class="hero-headline-placeholder" aria-hidden="true">
    I grew up learning to sit with things I didn&rsquo;t understand yet.
    <span class="hero-headline-em">I still do.</span>
  </span>
  <span class="hero-headline-typer">
    <span id="typeText"></span>
    <span class="hero-headline-em" id="typeTextEm"></span>
    <span class="text-type-cursor"></span>
  </span>
</h1>

.hero-headline { position: relative; }
.hero-headline-placeholder { visibility: hidden; display: block; pointer-events: none; }
.hero-headline-typer { position: absolute; inset: 0; display: block; }
.text-type-cursor {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 0.05em; height: 0.85em;
  background: #c9a96e;
  margin-left: 0.05em;
  vertical-align: text-bottom;
  border-radius: 1px;
  animation: ttBlink 0.85s steps(2, start) infinite;
}
@keyframes ttBlink { 0%,50% { opacity: 1; } 51%,100% { opacity: 0; } }

8.9 Reduced-motion master rule
Always ship this block:

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  html { scroll-behavior: auto; }
  .reveal, .reveal-stagger > *, .hero-load,
  .project-card, .project-featured,
  .link-anim::after, .thought-item, .portrait-wrap {
    opacity: 1 !important;
    transform: none !important;
    transition: none !important;
    animation: none !important;
  }
  .scroll-progress, .hero-particles canvas,
  .blob-cursor-container, .blob-svg-filter { display: none; }
}

