10. Content & Voice Conventions
Not strictly "design" but inseparable from it:

Section intros are short and confident. One or two sentences of primary prose (text-lg text-text-primary), then secondary prose (text-sm text-text-muted).
Lead with a question or a principle. Avoid "I am…" openers.
Italics in gold are reserved for the 2–5 most important words on a page.
Captions describe context, not content. Sahyadri School (KFI), Pune, not Photo of school.
Stats are given in mono font inline: depth 10 → ~530,000 nodes, 1,700× reduction.
Never use emojis.
Links open in new tabs for external destinations, include target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer".
11. File & Asset Conventions
Images: kebab-case filenames (pandav-patthar.jpg, portrait-bw.png). Avoid spaces and apostrophes — browsers need encoding and it breaks casually.
Photo aspect ratios: Pick one of ratio-16-9, ratio-4-3, ratio-3-4, ratio-1-1. Never free-form.
Loading: loading="lazy" on every image except hero portrait (loading="eager").
Object-position: Tall portraits in square/circle frames need object-position: 50% 0%. Landscape portraits in 4:3 frames with the subject off-center need explicit object-position: left center or similar — always verify the subject isn't cropped.
.nojekyll at repo root for GitHub Pages (prevents Jekyll from eating underscore-prefixed files).
Favicon: a single SVG.
12. Technology Constraints
No build step. Tailwind CDN only. No npm, no bundler, no framework.
Vanilla JavaScript. No jQuery, no React, no Vue. IntersectionObserver + addEventListener.
Two HTML files per concept max: a summary (index.html) and a detail (projects.html), linked by link-anim.
All styles inline in one <style> tag per page. No external CSS files (beyond fonts/Tailwind CDN).
All JS inline in one <script> tag at the bottom of body.
Accessibility: every animation gated on prefers-reduced-motion; every image has an alt; every interactive element is a real <a> or <button>.
13. Cross-reference: Games Repo
The games repo (rachitagrawal146.github.io/game-algorithms-java) is a sibling of the portfolio, hosted on GitHub Pages from a separate repo, and is linked from the portfolio's featured project card. It is expected to share this same design language — same colours, same fonts, same noise overlay, same section labels, same photo/card/insight-box components. The detail page layout (projects.html on the portfolio) is the closest reference for how long-form technical content should look: numbered project blocks separated by hairline borders, .subhead mono labels in gold, .insight-box callouts, .metrics tables, and a centered footer row of mono links back to GitHub and demos.

If you're building a new page for either repo, start from the skeleton in §9, paste the component blocks from §6 that you need, and you will automatically be consistent.

Bottom line for any new page:

#0c0c0b background, noise overlay, 760px content column.
Cormorant Garamond italic display + Inter body + DM Mono labels.
Every section numbered NN — Title in gold mono 10px wide-tracked.
Gold (#c9a96e) accent only — for italic heading words, labels, borders, glows.
Hairline dividers between sections (rgba(255,255,255,0.07) at 0.5px).
Scroll reveals + shiny-text sweep + portrait halo = the motion vocabulary.
Respect prefers-reduced-motion on every animation.
No build tools. Tailwind CDN + vanilla JS + one HTML file per page.
